Function: fflog
Section: number_theoretical
C-Name: fflog
Prototype: GGDG
Help: fflog(x,g,{o}): return the discrete logarithm of the finite field
 element x in base g. If present, o must be the the multiplicative
 order of g or its factorisation matrix. If no o is given, assume that g is a
 primitive root.
Doc: discrete logarithm of the finite field element $x$ in base $g$. If
 present, $o$ must be the multiplicative order of $g$, or its factorisation
 matrix.  If no $o$ is given, assume that $g$ is a primitive root.
 \bprog
 ? t = ffgen(ffinit(7,5));
 ? o = fforder(t)
 %2 = 5602   \\@com \emph{not} a primitive root.
 ? fflog(t^10,t)
 %3 = 11214  \\@com indeed correct modulo o
 ? fflog(t^10,t, o)
 %4 = 10
 @eprog
